text: Göztepe Spor Kulübü (, Göztepe Sports Club) also known as Göztepe, is a Turkish sports club based in the Göztepe and Güzelyalı neighborhoods of İzmir. The club became the Turkish champions in 1950. In 1969 Göztepe became the first Turkish football team to play a semi-final in European competitions. ==References== Category:2000s establishments in Turkey Category:2008 establishments in Asia Category:2008 establishments in Europe Category:Turkish football clubs
